// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/lfcyz8 two interlocked tetrahedra grids, 2024 by jt
// using https://www.shadertoy.com/view/lXGGR3 raymarch voxels with color

// Tetrahedra placed in voxels form two interlocked grids.
// Square beams or hexagonal beams fit between the gaps.
// TODO: Check if rhombic dodecahedra can be placed along edges of one grid.

// Related (scaled up) variant: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/lcccz8 interlocked flip tetrahedra grid

// Possibly related to https://www.shadertoy.com/view/l3GGR3 seven direction pencil structure

// Possibly related to Gyroid https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gyroid
// Possibly related to Schwarz minimal surfaces https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schwarz_minimal_surface
// Possibly related to Schoen F-RD https://minimalsurfaces.blog/home/repository/triply-periodic/schoen-f-rd/

// tags: 3d, grid, raymarch, sdf, voxel, tetrahedra, tetrahedron, dda, hybrid, interlocked

